Melt butter in large saucepan. Add onion, carrot, celery, pepper, apple, and chicken. Cook until browned. Stir in flour, curry powder, mace, cloves, parsley, and tomatoes. Cover, and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Take chicken out, set aside, and strain vegetables from broth. Return chicken to pot. Using a food mill, puree vegetables. Return to soup. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add rice and boiling white stock. Serve.